Job Description:
• Daily acquisition of all Ariston subsidiaries needs through analysis of the Stock Transfer Requests and Orders and Customers Orders Portfolio;
• Products availability checks to guarantee correct allocation for fulfilling Stock Transfer Orders;
• Outbound delivery creation in SAP containing product codes/quantities to be shipped;
• Define the best loading capacity for every single shipment;
• Shipment planning;
• Orders monitoring and information sharing with subsidiaries and commercial colleagues;
• Manage possible production delays and multi-market requests;
• Provide support to the Warehouse department to make the shipment happen;
• Monitor Warehouse loadings;
• Monitor Carriers’ picking at requested date;
• Monitor Carriers’ performances;
• Guarantee carrier’s agreed transport tariff;
• Invoice issuing;
• Customs documents preparation (certificate of origin/licences/liquidation);
• Support to Local logistics for inquiries on orders/shipments;
• Management of returns, loading discrepancies, scraps due to transport damages, recovery from suppliers;
• Measure and compare Level of Service and Economics to target levels
• Comply with the company's regulations, and regulations on fire prevention, occupational safety and health
• Implement other allowable tasks assigned by Supply chain & Logistics Manager.

1. THÔNG TIN CHUNG
